{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WucPfQeuN5Be3v83JRhB2n","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 37 — state corruption fix #21, no-op (2026-03-27T15:59Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **State corruption fix #21**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n     6→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n     7→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n     8→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph stale in-memory state overwrites. 21st occurrence.\n     9→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    10→\n    11→## Token Report\n    12→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    13→- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 4, Edit: 5\n    14→- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n    15→- Redundant operations: None — efficient fix of known recurring issue\n    16→\n    17→### Session 34 — state corruption fix #18, no-op (2026-03-27T15:48Z)\n    18→\n    19→- **State corruption fix #18**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, epic-16 at `backlog`. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist in `verification/`.\n    20→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done` in sprint-status.yaml.\n    21→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This has been the same issue since session 31+. The fix deployed in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent ralph from reverting statuses of existing stories.\n    22→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    23→\n    24→## Token Report\n    25→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    26→- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 5, Glob: 1, Grep: 0\n    27→- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n    28→- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue\n    29→\n    30→### Session 35 — state corruption fix #19, no-op (2026-03-27T19:51Z)\n    31→\n    32→- **State corruption fix #19**: Identical pattern to session 34 — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, sprint done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n    33→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n    34→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n    35→- **Root cause**: Ralph's stale in-memory state continues overwriting sprint-state.json. The `registerStory` guard doesn't prevent status reversion of existing stories.\n    36→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    37→\n    38→## Token Report\n    39→- Total tool calls: ~8\n    40→- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 3, Edit: 3, Glob: 1, Write: 1\n    41→- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n    42→- Redundant operations: None\n    43→\n    44→### Session 36 — state corruption fix #20, no-op (2026-03-27T20:00Z)\n    45→\n    46→- **State corruption fix #20**: Identical pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, sprint done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n    47→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n    48→- Fixed by parent orchestrator: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70->74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n    49→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph stale in-memory state overwrites. 20th occurrence. No code fix deployed.\n    50→- **6th consecutive no-op session.** Sprint complete since session 30. Ralph needs to be killed.\n    51→\n    52→## Token Report\n    53→- Total tool calls: ~8\n    54→- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 5, Edit: 2\n    55→- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n    56→- Redundant operations: None\n    57→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f770fc3a-ce75-489b-afd1-73b55d088f5e","uuid":"fb55d06e-6478-4b7d-badd-8cba2bfaf461","timestamp":"2026-03-27T16:03:07.288Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 37 — state corruption fix #21, no-op (2026-03-27T15:59Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #21**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph stale in-memory state overwrites. 21st occurrence.\n- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 4, Edit: 5\n- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None — efficient fix of known recurring issue\n\n### Session 34 — state corruption fix #18, no-op (2026-03-27T15:48Z)\n\n- **State corruption fix #18**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, epic-16 at `backlog`. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist in `verification/`.\n- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done` in sprint-status.yaml.\n- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This has been the same issue since session 31+. The fix deployed in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents new phantoms